To adjust the code so that when discrete breaks have names, they'll be used as labels by default, we need to modify how labels are derived for discrete scales in the `AxisSecondary` ggproto object. Specifically, we want to make sure that if the primary axis has named breaks, those names will be applied as labels to the secondary axis unless explicitly overridden.

Here's how you can modify the relevant parts of the code:

1. Modify the `init` function in the `AxisSecondary` ggproto object to handle named breaks:

```r
init = function(self, scale) {
  if (self$empty()) {
    return()
  }
  transform <- self$trans
  if (!is.function(transform)) {
    cli::cli_abort("Transformation for secondary axes must be a function.")
  }
  if (is.derived(self$name) && !is.waiver(scale$name)) self$name <- scale$name
  if (is.derived(self$breaks)) self$breaks <- scale$breaks
  if (is.waiver(self$breaks)) {
    if (scale$is_discrete()) {
      self$breaks <- scale$get_breaks()
    } else {
      breaks <- scale$get_transformation()$breaks
      n_breaks <- scale$n.breaks
      if (!is.null(n_breaks) && "n" %in% fn_fmls_names(breaks)) {
        self$breaks <- function(x) breaks(x, n = n_breaks)
      } else {
        self$breaks <- breaks
      }
    }
  }
  if (is.waiver(self$labels)) {
    if (scale$is_discrete() && !is.null(names(self$breaks))) {
      self$labels <- names(self$breaks)
    } else if (is.derived(self$labels)) {
      self$labels <- scale$labels
    }
  }
  if (is.derived(self$guide)) self$guide <- scale$guide
}
```

2. Explain any changes:

- **Labels Default Logic**: In the `init()` method, when checking `is.waiver(self$labels)`, we first examine if the primary axis is discrete and if the breaks have names. If so, use those names as labels by default. This takes advantage of the R feature where named vectors can be used to assign labels for axes by directly adopting the names as labels if no other labels are provided.

- **Fallback to Default Labels**: If no names exist, it still defaults to using the derived labels from the primary axis.

